e. The critical point from Higgs\ncondensation has a categorical symmetry formed by a $Z_2$ 0-symmetry and its\ndual - a $Z_2$ 2-symmetry, while the critical point of the confinement\ntransition has a categorical symmetry formed by a $Z_2$ 1-symmetry and its dual\n- another $Z_2$ 1-symmetry.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 31 Dec 2019 18:46:37 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 7 Jan 2020 02:42:18 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Sat, 30 May 2020 13:25:29 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Thu, 17 Sep 2020 22:09:00 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-09-23"}
